
Enter a URL into a web browser
Browser looks up the IP address for the domain name via DNS.
Browser sends a HTTP request to the server.
Server sends back a HTTP response.
Browser begins rendering the HTML.
Browser sends requests for additional objects embedded in HTML (images, CSS, JavaScript) and repeats steps 3-5.
Once the page is loaded, the browser sends further asynchronous requests as needed.

-----------------------------------------------------------

Show graphic of site with file components

